ğŸ¤ Contributing

We welcome contributions that strengthen defensive drone security research.

Contribution Rules

âœ… Allowed:

Simulation-based research (SITL / HITL)

Firmware auditing and integrity validation

Protocol analysis and documentation

Detection, mitigation, and resilience techniques

Academic papers and standards references


ğŸš« Not Allowed:

RF jamming or interference tools

Live GPS spoofing or hijacking

Unauthorized access techniques

Instructions enabling real-world disruption


How to Contribute

1. Fork the repository


2. Create a feature branch


3. Add well-documented resources or labs


4. Include citations where applicable


5. Submit a pull request with a clear description




---

ğŸ§ª Hands-On PX4 & ArduPilot Security Labs

These labs are designed to be legal, repeatable, and simulation-first.

Lab 1: Firmware Integrity Verification

Build firmware from source

Verify hashes and signatures

Compare against deployed firmware (SITL)


Lab 2: Parameter Tamper Detection

Modify parameters in SITL

Observe system responses

Validate failsafe behavior


Lab 3: Telemetry Signing Validation

Enable MAVLink signing

Attempt unsigned message injection (simulation)

Confirm rejection and logging


Lab 4: Failsafe Trigger Analysis

Simulate RC loss

Simulate GPS degradation

Observe recovery logic


Lab 5: Navigation Resilience

Disable GNSS in SITL

Validate INS / vision fallback

Measure drift and recovery



---

ğŸ§  Threat Models

High-Level Threat Categories

Command & Control: message tampering, replay

Firmware: unauthorized modification, rollback

Navigation: GNSS degradation or deception

Sensors: spoofing, saturation, failure

Supply Chain: compromised components or updates


Defensive Controls Mapping

Threat	Mitigation

Telemetry replay	MAVLink signing
Firmware tampering	Secure boot + hashes
GNSS loss	Sensor fusion + failsafes
Sensor failure	Redundancy + validation



